<p>Pakistani authorities say they have arrested four suspects — including an alleged mastermind — in connection with a suicide bombing at a Shi’ite mosque (imambargah) in Islamabad that killed more than 30 people, according to multiple outlets citing official statements. Officials said the attacker detonated explosives at the mosque’s gate after Friday prayers. China condemned the attack and said it supports Pakistan’s efforts to safeguard national security and stability.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/JsYlX4r_-UP__WH4xyIw_4UASoN97Yh1lxw9YfBo8XQjBr-JnBXsQFF0Q-rkeUvMeSSK3IwdDZrh-dR3dEi75pAjW24Nejs4aBo4cYLSHRw3' alt='Security personnel cordon off the imambargah’s perimeter in Islamabad on February 7, 2026, a day after a suicide attack.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Deadliest in years: CBS News said the bombing was the deadliest suicide attack in Islamabad in nearly 20 years, underscoring how rare large attacks are in the capital.</li><li>Arrests described as a facilitation network: BBC said Interior Minister Mohsin Naqvi described the four detainees as suspected facilitators — including one he called the alleged mastermind — arrested in overnight raids.</li><li>Where it happened: Dawn said the blast struck Imambargah Qasr-i-Khadijatul Kubra in the Tarlai area, described as “rural Islamabad,” off Lehtrar Road.</li><li>Blast-scene details: Dawn said photos and video from the site showed bodies near the mosque’s front gate and debris scattered across the red-carpeted prayer hall.</li></ul><blockquote>China is deeply shocked by the deadly explosion in Pakistan’s capital Islamabad and the heavy casualties it has inflicted. - Chinese foreign ministry (statement)</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Pakistan interior ministry/government: Interior Minister Mohsin Naqvi said authorities arrested four alleged facilitators — including an alleged mastermind — in overnight raids, and said they were linked to IS-K. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cd6w69pj14xo'>BBC News</a>)</li><li>Dawn reporting: Dawn identified the target as Imambargah Qasr-i-Khadijatul Kubra in Islamabad’s Tarlai area, and described images from the scene showing bodies near the front gate and debris across the prayer hall. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1971847/china-condemns-islamabad-imambargah-attack-says-it-supports-pakistan-in-safeguarding-national-security'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>New York Times analysis: The New York Times described the bombing as a setback for Pakistan’s effort to show improving security after operations that reduced some militant violence. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/07/world/asia/pakistan-mosque-bombing.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/07/world/asia/pakistan-mosque-bombing.html'>A Mosque Bombing Undercuts Pakistan’s Bid for Security</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cd6w69pj14xo'>Alleged mastermind among four arrested after Pakistan mosque blast</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/islamic-state-affiliate-suspects-arrested-pakistan-mosque-suicide-bombing/'>4 suspects arrested after bombing at Pakistan mosque leaves 31 dead</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rferl.org/a/pakistan-mosque-attack-arrests-funerals-islamabad/33672178.html'>Pakistani Authorities Make First Arrests After Deadly Mosque Attack</a> - rferl.org</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2026/02/07/nx-s1-5704332/suicide-bombing-at-islamabad-mosque-kills-31-people'>Suicide bombing at Islamabad mosque kills 31 people</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://apnews.com/article/pakistan-shiite-mosque-islamabad-islamic-state-claim-8d5749cddcb65228bfd3d38e799f8acd'>Pakistani security forces arrest four people allegedly associated with the Khorasan Islamic State, accusing them of bombing the Shia mosque in Islamabad yesterday.</a> - apnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/putin-offers-cou